summary: This is a search warrant issued by the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York authorizing the search of a multi-story single-family residence in New York, NY. The warrant seeks evidence related to violations of sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy, specifically listing items such as taxidermied dogs, massage tables, photos of nude women, and a binder labeled 'NI Girls'.

persons.name: Barbara Moses
persons.context: Issued the search warrant for the premises related to sex trafficking violations.

events.title: Search Warrant Issued
events.description: A federal search warrant was issued authorizing the search of a multi-story single-family residence in New York, NY for evidence related to sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy.

locations: Multi-story single-family residence in New York, New York
keyFacts: The search warrant targets a residence for evidence of violations of Title 18, U.S. Code, Sections 371 (conspiracy) and 1591 (sex trafficking of minors).
Specific items to be seized include taxidermied dogs, massage tables, busts of female torsos, photos of nude women, sex toys, and a binder labeled 'NI Girls'.
The warrant was issued by Magistrate Judge Barbara Moses and had to be executed by May 7, 2019.
